Name: oculocutaneous albinism type IA
Definition: An oculocutaneous albinism that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive null mutation of TYR on chromosome 11q14.3 with no residual protein activity.

Name: oculocutaneous albinism type IB
Definition: An oculocutaneous albinism that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive hypomorphic mutation of TYR on chromosome 11q14.3 with retention of some residual protein activity.

Name: oculocutaneous albinism type II
Definition: An oculocutaneous albinism that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of OCA2 on chromosome 15q12-q13.

Name: oculocutaneous albinism type III
Definition: An oculocutaneous albinism that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of TYRP1 on chromosome 9p23.

Name: oculocutaneous albinism type IV
Definition: An oculocutaneous albinism that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of SLC45A2 on chromosome 5p13.2.

Name: oculocutaneous albinism type V
Definition: An oculocutaneous albinism that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of OCA5 on chromosome 4q24.

Name: oculocutaneous albinism type VII
Definition: An oculocutaneous albinism that has_material_basis_in an autosomal recessive mutation of C10orf11 on chromosome 10q22.2-q22.3.

Name: obsolete Noonan syndrome 1
